# Cursor — UI design only

Apply these instructions **only** when designing, styling, or building visual UI for this site.

**Do not apply** for config, content, analytics, scripts, or non-visual edits.

## Activation

- User asks to design UI, apply the design system, or change look and feel
- You are editing: `_sass/**`, `_includes/**`, `_layouts/**`, `assets/css/**`, `index.html`, `design/**`

## Source of truth

Read `design/design-system.md` before proposing UI changes.

## Stack

Jekyll + SCSS + HTML includes. Map design tokens to SCSS; match existing partials (`_sass/_base.scss`, skins, etc.).

## File-scoped rule

When working in UI paths, also follow `.cursor/rules/design-ui.mdc` (auto-attached via globs). Use @Codebase on `_sass/`, `_includes/`, and `_layouts/` for component context.
